CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 11, 1967, pg. 13, reads: "Daisy Lampkin Award - A highlight of the Awards Dinner-Dance sponsored by the NAACP Women's Auxiliary recently, was the presentation of the "Daisy E. Lampkin Award" to Mrs. Homer S. Brown, second from right shown accepting a silver bowl from Auxiliary President Mrs. Alma Fox while Mrs. C. Dolores Tucker of Philadelphia, mistress of ceremonies, left, and Mrs. Mary Gloster, general chairman, right, look on. - All Harris Photos."Accompanying article reads: "An overflow crowd packed the main ballroom of the Pick-Roosevelt Hotel recently when the Women's Auxiliary of the Pittsburgh Branch NAACP sponsored its second annual "Daisy E. Lampkin Award" Dinner-Dance..."
TitMainTitle: C. Dolores Tucker, Alma Speed presenting "Daisy Lampkin Award" bowl to Wilhelmina Byrd Brown, and Mary Gloster, at Women's Auxiliary of NAACP dinner dance, Roosevelt Hotel
